    <div class="document">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="section">
            <div class="title">Volunteer Policy</div>
            <div class="revision">Version: 0.01 (Draft)</div>
            <div class="review">Reviewed: July 3rd 2019 by Trustees</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="section">
            <div class="section-title">Audience</div>
            <p>This policy applies to any and all persons undertaking activities on behalf of PlaySchule including, but not limited to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Trustees</li>
              <li>Project Managers</li>
              <li>Developemnt Officers</li>
              <li>Volunteers</li>
              <li>Funders</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="section">
            <div class="section-title">Why Have A Volunteer Policy?</div>
            <p>A Volunteer Policy gives PlaySchule a consistent way to approach the involvement of volunteers across our whole organisation. It helps to ensure
              that everyone involved in the organisation understand and value volunteers’ involvement.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="section">
            <div class="section-title">Legal Framework</div>
            <p>This policy has been drawn up on the basis of law and guidance that seeks to value and protect our members, volunteers and staff, namely:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>The Equality Act of 2010</li>
              <li>The Health &amp; Safety At Work Act of 1974</li>
              <li>Relevant Government &amp; Staturotry Guidance On Volunteering</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="section">
            <div class="section-title">Volunteer Definition</div>
            <p>Volunteers are entirely different to employees and workers. This is the NCVO definition of volunteering:</p>
            <q>…any activity that involves spending time, unpaid, doing something that aims to benefit the environment or someone (individuals or groups) other than, or in addition to, close relatives.</q>
            <p>Unlike an employee or worker, a volunteer:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>does not give their time or skills under contract</li>
              <li>is unpaid</li>
              <li>is not entitled to protection from employment law.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="section">
            <div class="section-title">In Practise</div>
            <p>We will seek to eunsure best practicies by:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Develop this policy in consultation with staff and volunteers and be reviewed on a regular basis to ensure that it continues to be fit for purpose.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
